.TH LSFONTS 1 "May 2026" "lsfonts 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lsfonts \- list installed fonts with rendered previews
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lsfonts
[\fB\-l\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR | \fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-h\fR | \fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lsfonts
scans the standard system font directories, parses every
.IR .otf ,
.IR .ttf ,
and
.IR .ttc
file it finds, and shows one card per face in a scrollable, searchable list.
Each card renders the family and style header in a sans-serif UI font and
shows a sample line ("AaBbCc 0123 The quick brown fox\(em") in the font
itself, so the typeface can be evaluated at a glance.
.PP
When the terminal supports an inline image protocol
.RB ( Kitty ,
.BR iTerm2 ,
or
.BR Sixel )
lsfonts opens an interactive browser. Otherwise it falls back to a plain
text listing equivalent to
.B "lsfonts \-l" .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-l
Print a plain text listing (one font per line, family/style and path
separated by a tab) to standard output and exit. Useful for piping into
other tools.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the lsfonts version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.SH "INTERACTIVE KEYS"
.TP
.BR Up ", " Down ", " k ", " j
Move the selection one card. The arrow keys also work while the filter
prompt is open, so the user can scroll through matches without leaving
search mode.
.TP
.BR PgUp ", " PgDn ", " Space ", " b
Move one page (Space pages forward, b pages back).
.TP
.BR g ", " Home
Jump to the first card.
.TP
.BR G ", " End
Jump to the last card.
.TP
.B /
Open the incremental, case-insensitive substring filter on family name and
file path. Any existing query is preserved so the filter can be refined
rather than retyped.
.TP
.B Enter
Keep the current filter and leave the prompt. The active filter remains
visible in the status bar.
.TP
.BR Backspace ", " Ctrl-U
Inside the prompt: delete one character / clear the whole query while
remaining in search mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl-C
Copy the selected entry's name to the system clipboard in a portable
"Family Style" form (e.g.
.IR "DejaVu Sans Mono Bold" ),
suitable for dropping straight into CSS
.RB ( "font-family: \(dqDejaVu Sans Mono Bold\(dq;" ),
Vim/Neovim
.RB ( "set guifont=DejaVu\e Sans\e Mono\e Bold:h11" ),
or Pango/GTK font strings. A confirmation flash is shown in the status bar.
On systems with no clipboard backend (no
.BR wl-copy (1),
.BR xclip (1),
.BR xsel (1),
.BR pbcopy (1)
or
.BR clip.exe ),
the flash reports the failure.
.TP
.B Esc
Inside the prompt: cancel search and clear the filter. Outside the prompt:
clear an active filter; if no filter is active, quit.
.TP
.BR q ", " Ctrl-D
Quit unconditionally.
.SH "GRAPHICS DETECTION"
The image protocol is selected from the environment:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B Kitty
when
.B TERM
is
.IR xterm-kitty .
.IP \[bu] 2
.B iTerm2
when
.B TERM_PROGRAM
is
.IR iTerm.app .
.IP \[bu] 2
.B Sixel
when
.B TERM
starts with
.IR foot ", " mlterm ", " yaft ", " contour ", or " wezterm .
.PP
Setting
.B NO_COLOR
disables graphics and forces the plain text fallback.
.SH FILES
.PP
.B Linux
.RS
.IR /usr/share/fonts ,
.IR /usr/local/share/fonts ,
.IR ~/.local/share/fonts ,
.IR ~/.fonts
.RE
.PP
.B FreeBSD / OpenBSD / NetBSD / DragonFly
.RS
.IR /usr/local/share/fonts ,
.IR /usr/X11R7/lib/X11/fonts ,
.IR /usr/pkg/share/fonts ,
.IR ~/.local/share/fonts ,
.IR ~/.fonts
.RE
.PP
.B macOS
.RS
.IR /Library/Fonts ,
.IR /System/Library/Fonts ,
.IR /System/Library/Fonts/Supplemental ,
.IR ~/Library/Fonts
.RE
.PP
.B Windows
.RS
.IR %WINDIR%\eFonts ,
.IR %LOCALAPPDATA%\eMicrosoft\eWindows\eFonts
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
No fonts were found in the standard directories, or the interactive UI
failed to start.
.TP
.B 2
A command-line option could not be parsed.
.SH AUTHOR
Alexander F. R\(/odseth
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR fc-list (1),
.BR fc-match (1),
.BR fc-cache (1)
